deals.highlightsHtml: Learn the graceful, musical art of tap dance with up to 20 classes
deals.pitchHtml:
Choose Between Two Options

  • $65 for 10 Adult Tap Dance Classes ($135 value)
  • $125 for 20 Adult Tap Dance Classes ($270 value)

####Tap Shoes: Making Music, Step by Step

Before you shuffle off to your first tap class, you’ll want to secure the proper footwear. Use Groupon’s study of tap shoes to ensure your feet can keep the beat.

It’s hard to imagine Bill “Bojangles” Robinson dancing across the silver screen in 1935 with bottle caps nailed to his shoes, but that might have been the case if it weren’t for a breakthrough in dance just a decade earlier. Modern tap shoes—with their smooth, endlessly customizable metal plates in the toe and heel—made their mainstream debut in the 1925 show No, No Nanette, and within a few years, most Broadway-style dancers were amplifying their steps with the help of metal plates. The style known simply as tap existed before that, of course, but tappers had to practice their craft wearing clogs, boots, or hard-soled shoes outfitted with hobnails or bottle caps. Like many American styles, the moves were a fusion of different cultures, combining irish clog dancing and english step dancing with the improvisational, rhythmic dances passed down through generations of African Americans. The dance quickly spread throughout social clubs, street corners, and eventually traveling minstrel shows before hitting Broadway and, from there, Hollywood.

Today, men’s tap shoes echo the black, Oxford-style shoe worn by Robinson himself, while women’s tap shoes often mimic the girlish, Mary Jane flats of his frequent dance partner, Shirley Temple. Women’s shoes are also available in heels, though beginners may find them too difficult to use at first. Most tappers recommend leather shoes with metal plates, but more affordable options made of PVC or polyurethane make for a decent starter pair. Some vendors may sell the taps separately from the shoe; these require professional attachment, though they allow dancers to loosen or tighten the plates at will to customize their individual sound.

deals.pitchHtml:
Get lost in a world of books. Open to the public since May 2017, this cool new museum immerses you in a wonderland of words through cutting-edge technology, tracing the history of U.S. literature, as well as other forms of writing, from songs and ad slogans to poetry and sci-fi. In addition to fascinating revolving exhibits, you'll delve into the actual creative process, with a collaborative story area (complete with pencils, typewriters and digital access), a kid lit gallery and the Anatomy of a Masterwork, which takes you into the mind of an author. And for all you logophiles (word lovers) out there, there's even a game room featuring interactive tabletop consoles.

The tickets identified in this promotion are made available through Goldstar. Groupon is not affiliated with or sponsored by American Writers Museum in connection with this deal.

This offer is not eligible for promo codes.

deals.highlightsHtml: Hair festival is open to hair care professionals, barbers, students, and hair salon owners with marketplace and product demos included
deals.pitchHtml:
Choice of:

  • Two Consumer Admission Passes
  • Four Consumer Admission Passes
  • Two Licensed Professional Admission Passes
  • Two Beauty/Barber College Student Admission Passes
  • Two Natural Hair and Barbering Competition General Admission Ticket
  • Two VIP Natural Hair Fest and Competition Package Tickets

Styling Products” should read Natural Hair Fest Chicago Mid-Winter 2018

Welcome to a world of Natural Hair and Beauty Culture, Natural Hair Fest Chicago Mid-Winter 2018 - Open To The Public, Natural Hair Care Professionals, Barbers, Students and Natural Hair Salon Owners. Join the fun and excitement on Sunday January 14th with a Natural Hair Marketplace, Classes, Product Demos, Panel Discussions, Fashion Modeling, Spoken Word, Live Entertainment and much more.

Natural Hair Fest Chicago is designed to promote a way of life that nurtures natural hair growth and teaches proper regimens for the care and maintenance of healthy, natural hair. We are equally concerned about beginning the process of healing and taking preventative measures to offset hair loss and disorders of the scalp that plague our communities in epidemic proportion.

We summit to pin-point, intercept, negate and correct mis-education, mis-information, and bad habits that lead to challenges associated with managing coarse, curly, kinky, coily and multi-textured hair types.

Natural Hair Fest Chicago is a one-stop destination where Consumers will be able to meet up and make conscious, person to person connections with skilled, Instructors, business-minded Professionals, Freelancers and Students in attendance who specialize in natural hair care.

The Activities: Fashion Show, Competition, Hair Care Classes and Forums, Live Entertainment, Free Product Demos, Spoken Poetry Special and much more.

deals.highlightsHtml: During 3–4-hour workshop, students will test out their photo skills while touring the city and learning basic photography concepts
deals.pitchHtml:
Choose from Three Options

  • $65 for City Muse Tour for one ($130 value)
  • $125 for City Muse Tour for two ($260 value)
  • $245 for City Muse Tour for four ($520 value)

After an hour introduction to digital photography techniques, instructors will take students on a tour of the city’s iconic places and hidden pockets to help them put their newfound photo skills to the test. Along the way, participants will learn basic photography techniques and artistic composition, as well as digital camera operation, lighting techniques, and the use of color and texture to make images pop. 

Participants must provide their own camera and car. Car-Pooling is encouraged.
